binaries are unmodified Debian packages, the corresponding source is available
from Debian's published sources for the matching package versions.


Bundled components
------------------

1. jlesage/baseimage-gui (base image)
   License : MIT
   Source  : https://github.com/jlesage/docker-baseimage-gui
   Provides: TigerVNC, noVNC, NGINX, Openbox, and the container init system.

2. k3b  (KDE CD / DVD / Blu-ray burning suite)
   License : GPL-2.0-or-later
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/k3b
   Upstream: https://apps.kde.org/k3b/

3. cdrdao  (disc-at-once engine used by K3b for audio mastering)
   License : GPL-2.0-or-later
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/cdrdao
   Upstream: https://cdrdao.sourceforge.net/

4. cdrkit / wodim  (data-CD backend)
   License : GPL-2.0-only
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/cdrkit

5. dvd+rw-tools  (DVD / Blu-ray backend, growisofs)
   License : GPL-2.0-or-later
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/dvd+rw-tools

6. adwaita-qt  (Qt theme for dark mode)
   License : LGPL-2.1-or-later
   Source  : https://tracker.debian.org/pkg/adwaita-qt


Source availability
-------------------

To obtain the complete corresponding source for any GPL/LGPL component above,
fetch the matching Debian source package, for example:

   apt-get source k3b

run against a Debian 12 (bookworm) apt source list, or browse the Debian source
tracker links listed above. The exact package versions in any given build are
those present in the Debian 12 archive at image build time.
